        <div class="jerusalem">
          <h3>Jerusalem</h3>
          <p>Jerusalem is the capital of Israel and one of the oldest cities in the world. It is an extremely holy city for many religions including Judaism, Islam and Christianity. Sacred sites include The Western Wall, The al-Aqsa Mosque and The Church of the Holy Sepulchre.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tel-aviv">
          <h3>Tel Aviv:</h3>
          <p>Tel Aviv is the second most populous city in Israel after Jerusalem. The city is Israel's economic hub and is also known for it's lively nightlife and beautiful beaches!</p>
        </div>

        <div class="haifa">
          <h3>Haifa:</h3>
          <p>Haifa is the third most populous city in Israel. It is known for it's tremendous beaches and is also the center of the Bahá'í faith.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="dead-sea">
          <h3>The Dead Sea:</h3>
          <p>The Dead Sea is located in the Jordan Rift Valley. As it's surface and shores are 430.5 metres below sea level, it is Earth's lowest elevation on land!</p>
        </div>
      </div>

